  "texts": [
    "In this case, the Jaccard index can be considered a relative measure, since the same approach is applied to each model.",
    "The above measures still miss some semantic nuances because certain concepts or observations (e.g., diseases, tissues, cells) may be expressed in complex phrases, possibly even involving negations.",
    "To remedy this, we use BioBERT 33 fine-tuned 63 for natural language inference and semantic textual similarity assessments.",
    "This embedding model provides the feature vectors of the generated report and the ground truth, allowing us to compute their cosine similarity as a measure of semantic understanding.",
    "To go beyond the domainspecific use of language, we apply a general large-scale embedding model, GPT-3-ADA 25, to capture a broader range of linguistic information."
  ],
